<table align="center" width="900" cellspacing="1"  cellpadding="10" border="0" bgcolor="#FFFFF0">
<tr><td><div>

<font size="+4" color=#990000>In Spanish</font> reflexive verbs can also be identified by the use of  
<font color="#0A14C4"><strong>reflexive pronouns</strong></font>
<br>
<br>
<table align="center" cellpadding=10" bgcolor="#D7EBD7" width="90%">

<tr>
<td><div>Yo</div></td><td><div><font color="#0A14C4"><strong>me</strong></font> &nbsp;afeito</div></td>
<td width="40"><div>&nbsp;</div></td>
<td><div>I shave</div></td><td><div>myself</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><div>T&uacute;</div></td><td><div><font color="#0A14C4"><strong>te</strong></font> &nbsp;afeitas</div></td>
<td width="40"><div>&nbsp;</div></td>
<td><div>You shave</div></td><td><div>yourself</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><div>El</div></td><td><div><font color="#0A14C4"><strong>se</strong></font> &nbsp;afeita</div></td>
<td width="40"><div>&nbsp;</div></td>
<td><div>He shaves</div></td><td><div>himself</div></td>
</tr>
</table>

<br>
Note that the placement of the reflexive pronoun is different from English.



</div></td></tr>







